parts.content:
The `ultralytics/nn/modules/conv.py` file within the Ultralytics repository defines various convolutional modules used in their deep learning models.

Some of the convolutional modules defined in this file include:

*   `Conv`
*   `Conv2`
*   `LightConv`
*   `DWConv`
*   `DWConvTranspose2d`
*   `ConvTranspose`
*   `Focus`
*   `GhostConv`
*   `RepConv`
*   `ChannelAttention`
*   `SpatialAttention`
*   `CBAM`
*   `Concat`
*   `Index`
*   `autopad`

You can find more detailed information and the source code for these modules at [ultralytics/nn/modules/conv.py](https://github.com/ultralytics/ultralytics/blob/main/ultralytics/nn/modules/conv.py).
